    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft rear groove snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300731">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300731" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300731" filename="../figg13/g1300731.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Remove Mainshaft Rear Groove Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary drive gear and washer from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300732">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300732" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300732" filename="../figg13/g1300732.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Remove Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary bearing retainer ring bolts and bearing retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300733">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300733" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300733" filename="../figg13/g1300733.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Remove Auxiliary Bearing Retainer Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splined washer from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300733">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully tap the auxiliary bearing rearward.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a pry bar and work the bearing out of the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300734">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300734" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300734" filename="../figg13/g1300734.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Work Bearing Out of Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the bearing and spacer. If the parts have been damaged, press the spacer out of the
                bearing and replace the parts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300734">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
